   <body>
      <p>Capturing signatures is easy with AppSheet. Simply insert a
    column in your spreadsheet with the word "Signature" as the
    <xref href="205319168-Effective-use-of-column-headers.dita">column
    header</xref> where you would like the signature pad to appear in
    the form. AppSheet will automatically detect this new column as
    a Signature Type after you <xref href="205318928-Column-structure.dita" scope="external">regenerate
    column structure</xref>.</p>
      <p>Alternatively, you can name the column anything you like and
    change the Column Type to Signature manually in
    the Advanced Editor&gt;Data&gt;Column Structure tab.</p>
      <p>The Drawing type is similar to Signature, but provides a
    larger canvas and colored pens in order to capture free-form
    sketches within the app.</p>
